    |:---:|:---:|:---:|
    | 5 | 6.04 | 9.5% |
    | 50 | 5.91 | 10.0% |
    | 200 | 5.56 | 10.6% |
    
    **Conclusion: FAIL.** The prime gap sequence is spectrally near-uniform. There are no hidden periodicities to exploit. Even 200 Fourier components reconstruct only 10.6% of gaps correctly. The quantum Fourier transform has nothing to find here because the gaps are essentially non-periodic. This is consistent with the pseudorandom nature of primes.
    
