    - But error scaling is alpha ~ 0.0 to 0.4 (sub-logarithmic, not polynomial convergence)
    - No universal sparse subset exists: cross-validation shows zero importance is x-dependent
    - Participation ratio stays ~33-64 (out of 100 zeros), no sparsity collapse
    - Prony/ESPRIT recovers only 2-5 of first 10 zeta zeros from psi(x) samples
    
