### Key New Results (Session 7)

| Finding | Significance |
|---------|-------------|
| **Cross-paradigm convergence** (8 paradigms) | Same barrier from AIT, CAs, type theory, topos, hypercomputation, CRT, reverse math, complexity |
| **K(p(n)\|n) >= 178 bits** for n=10^100 | Formal Kolmogorov complexity lower bound |
| **SNARG verification**: 50K ops to verify | But 10^68 ops to COMPUTE — gap is inherent |
| **Quantum: O(x^{1/3})** best possible | Proven Ω(√x) quantum lower bound; still 10^25× too slow |
| **Succinct structures**: 10^100 bits minimum | Exceeds atoms in universe by 10^20× |
| **Function field duality** | Z has infinite "genus" vs finite for F_q[t] — deepest structural explanation |
| **No self-similarity** | FFT detects zeta zeros but signal is aperiodic |
| **δ(n) mod m uniform** | CRT reconstruction of correction impossible |
| **1536 CA rules tested** | 0 generate primes |

