    | 100,000 | error 168 | error 850 | error 2103 | **DIVERGING** |
    
    **The sum is getting WORSE with more zeros.** This is the conditional convergence
    problem -- the explicit formula sum oscillates with growing amplitude before
    cancellation. You need ALL ~sqrt(x) zeros for the cancellation to work, and partial
    sums are unreliable.
    
    This is actually a well-known issue with the explicit formula (see Riesel & Gohl 1970).
    The convergence requires careful summation techniques (Cesaro/Abel summation) and
    fundamentally needs ~sqrt(x) terms to reach O(1) accuracy.
    
