    ## 6. The Summation Problem
    
    This is the TRUE killer, independent of all the above.
    
    ### The explicit formula
    
        pi(x) = R(x) - sum_{rho} R(x^rho) - 1/ln(2) + integral_x^infty dt / (t*(t^2-1)*ln(t))
    
    where the sum is over ALL nontrivial zeros rho = 1/2 + i*gamma (assuming RH).
    
    ### Why ~sqrt(x) terms are needed
    
    The truncation error from using N zeros is:
    
        |error| ~ x^{1/2} / (2*pi) * sum_{k=N+1}^{infty} 1/gamma_k
    
    For the error to be < 1 (needed for exact pi(x)):
    
        N ~ sqrt(x) / (2*pi)
    
    For x = 10^100: N ~ 1.6 * 10^{49} zeros needed.
    
