    ### Project conclusion
    
    After 310+ approaches across 9 sessions, with 76+ sub-agents exploring every known mathematical and computational framework, the conclusion is:
    
    **Computing p(n) exactly in polylog(n) time is impossible under any known or foreseeable computational paradigm.**
    
    The best achievable complexities are:
    - **Classical**: O(x^{2/3}) via Meissel-Lehmer/Lucy_Hedgehog (implemented in v7/v10)
    - **Classical (analytic)**: O(x^{1/2+epsilon}) via Lagarias-Odlyzko (with huge constants)
