**CRITICAL FINDING from the information theory agent!**

The correction δ(n) = p(n) - R^{-1}(n) requires only **O(log n) BITS** — NOT O(√n) bits as previously claimed. The barrier is **COMPUTATIONAL**, not information-theoretic:

- Information needed: O(log n) bits (range of δ is ~√p(n), encoding = log(√p) bits)
- Computation needed: finding those bits appears to require O(x^{2/3}) time
- **But there's NO proof this can't be done faster!** Lower bound is only Ω(log x)

This means the problem is NOT proven impossible — it's an open question! Let me check the other wave 2 agents and explore this further.
